{"id": "act_1774901652859_b3nliv", "timestamp": "2026-03-30T20:14:12.859Z", "source": "meeting", "type": "meeting_complete", "summary": "Meeting complete: Activity Feed Design: What Should It Show and Who Is It For? ï¿½ The activity feed was added as a shared log for worker, meeting, and interactive activity. It currently has 6 entries and sits in the meeting list page. Before building more logging, we need to decide: What activities are worth tracking? Who reads the feed (the user during a session? between sessions? the worker itself?)? Should it replace or complement the worker log? What format makes entries scannable vs noise? (6 decisions, 6 actions)", "linkedMeeting": "2026-03-30-design-review-activity-feed-design-what-should-it-show-and-who-is-it-for-t.md"}
